\c 112
\p
\q1
\v 1 Praise the Lord!
\q1 Blessed is the man who fears the Lord
\q1 In his commandments he delights greatly.
\q1
\v 2 Mighty in the land will be his seed
\q1 The generation of the upright will be blessed.
\q1
\v 3 Wealth and riches are in his house
\q1 And his righteousness stands forever.
\q1
\v 4 Light dawns in the darkness for the upright
\q1 He is gracious and merciful and righteous.
\q1
\v 5 It is well for the one who has mercy and lends
\q1 He conducts his matters with justice.
\q1
\v 6 For he will never be shaken
\q1 And for his remembrance will forever be righteous.
\q1
\v 7 A bad report he does not fear
\q1 His heart is secure
\q1 He trusts in the Lord.
\q1
\v 8 His heart is steadfast
\q1 He will not fear
\q1 Until he looks on his adversary.
\q1
\v 9 He has given generously, given to the poor
\q1 His righteousness will stand forever,
\q1 His horn is exalted in honor.
\q1
\v 10 The wicked one sees and is angry
\q1 His teeth he gnashes and wastes away
\q1 The desire of the wicked will perish.